INSIGHTS FROM TEST WICKETS

Introduction

Test cricket is the traditional format of cricket. Though there are some formats in cricket, Test format has a unique place in the cricket world for its uniqueness. Unlike other format, test cricket really tests the temperament, mindset and personality of the player.
The dataset we are going to look forth is 'Test Wickets' dataset. It is a rank based dataset and the rank is based on wickets. It has players from different countries and some data about them. 
We are going to see insights extracted from this data, what the data actually says, trends and patterns etc.,
Let's dive into this project.

print("The lower and upper fence of the Wickets distribution are {} and {} respectively.".format(lowfen, hifen))

Correlation

As the order of the data and the Rank is based on Wickets. We are looking for which feature affects the Wickets more.

The factors/features affecting Wickets could be:

  1. Career Span
  2. Matches
  3. Innings
  4. Balls
  5. Economy

As per the domain of the data, We cannot take Runs as a feature that affects wickets. Even if it does so, we can only say highest wicket takers gives more runs.

In [34]:
plt.figure(figsize= (10,5))
sns.heatmap(rawdf.corr(), cmap = 'vlag', annot = True, vmin = -1, vmax = 1,

CONCLUSION:

1) Australia have highest number of players.

2) Australia have highest wickets.

3) More players in a country, more wickets for that country.

4) The higher distribution of wickets is between 202 and 261. The mean of the wickets is 322.

5) Muthaiah Muralidaran have the highest number of wickets with 1st rank.

5) There are 7 bowlers in 500 wickets club. Australia and England has 2 bowlers each.

6) LR Hibbs from WestIndies is the Economical bowler.

7) The higher distribution of Economy rate is between 2.54 and 2.72. The average of Economy is 2.821.

8) WestIndies have Economical bowlers.

9) Almost all Distribution of other features are right-skewed.

10) Most experienced bowler- Imran Khan(PAK); Most matches & innings played- Jimmy Anderson(ENG); Most balls bowled- Muthiah Muralidaran(SL); Least runs given- VD Philander(SA).

11) Anil Kumble is the best test bowler in India followed by Ashwin.

12) BS Bedi is the Economical bowler in India.

13) SJ Harimson from England have the best figure among the Best figures and Saqlain Mushtaq is the least best figure among the Best figures.

14) Correlation between Matches and Innings is the highest and Runs and Economy is the lowest correlation.

15) Economy as a feature is not strongly correlated any other feature.

16) Balls is the predominant factor/feature affecting Wickets as it is highly correlated with Wickets.

17) Career Span is the least affecting factor/feature as it is has low correlation with Wickets.

18) Multi-Collinearity is prevalent among the factors/features. However, the feature Career Span is moderately correlated with other features.
